NonProportionalRIAgreement, ProportionalRIAgreement
@Generated(value="com.guidewire.pl.metadata.codegen.Codegen", comments="RIAgreement.eti;RIAgreement.eix;RIAgreement.etx") public abstract class RIAgreement extends com.guidewire.pl.persistence.code.BeanBase implements Validatable, Extractable, Retireable
RIAgreement Represents the contractual obligation of a reinsurer who has taken on some of the policy risk in exchange for some of the premium. The RIAgreement centralizes information related to that contract, detailing how the risk has been divided and ceded. Additionally, there is information to indicate when alerts should be directed to counterparties and users.

    • delete

      public void delete()
      If there are no RITransactions on the Agreement, this retires the RIAgreement. If there are RITransactions, then it disassociates the RIAgreement from the AgreementGroup. This effectively removes the RIAgreement from appearing in the UI.

      Also, if this is the last agreement in the agreement group, it will attempt to delete the group as well.

    • getPublicID

      public String getPublicID()
      The external ID for this entity.

      PublicID values are automatically created during the commit, if not previously set. The format is random, meeting security requirements based on current industry standards. For example:

      • pc:SYinDB2XTOgNZFs1NpxU8
      • pc:Sf8QS4N5RBS-h8_pj-Oy_
      • pc:SBwBzylneecSNr6_Ub4IO
      Your configuration code must not assume any particular format for PublicID values, in either the prefix or body portion of the string, or even assume the existence of a prefix. Do not make any assumptions at all about the content of a PublicID value, including expectations that values are sequential, numeric, or prefixed.

      You can subclass and override AbstractBundleTransactionCallback.afterSetIds(gw.pl.persistence.core.Bundle) if you need to see the value in the same commit. 

      
  var note = new Note(bundle)
  bundle.addBundleTransactionCallback(new AbstractBundleTransactionCallback() {
     override function afterSetIds(b : Bundle) {
       log.info("Created Note " + note.PublicID)
     }
  })

    • refresh

      public KeyableBean refresh()
      Refreshes this bean with the latest database version.

      This method does nothing if the bean is edited or inserted in its current bundle. If the bean no longer exists in the database, then null is returned. If the bean has been evicted from its bundle, then null is returned. Otherwise, this bean is returned, with its contents updated.

      public void reject(ValidationLevel errorLevel, String strErrorReason, ValidationLevel warningLevel, String strWarningReason)
      Rejects the root bean w/ a global message

      Note the reason why the bean failed validation shouldn't refer to a particular field in the entity. To do that, use the rejectField() method.

      Note you can indicate failure as both an error and a warning simultaneously. However, if the failure is both an error and a warning, the failure should have different error and warning levels.

    • remove

      public void remove()
      Marks this bean for remove. A bean marked for remove will be deleted or retired when the transaction is committed. Once a bean is marked for remove, it cannot be switched to update, edit, or read.

      WARNING: This method is designed for simple custom entities which are normally not associated with other entities. Undesirable results may occur when used on out-of-box entities.

    • touch

      public void touch()
      Set's the version of the bean to the next value (i.e. the bean version original value+1) Multiple calls to this method on the same bean will result in the same value being used for the version (i.e. it is idempotent). Calling this method will force the bean to be written to the database and participate fully in the commit cycle e.g. pre-update rules will be run, etc.
